<h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)</h2>
<p>
  To help you prepare for your journey, I have answered the 30 most common questions that solo travelers ask when planning a trip to Fort Kochi.
</p>

<div class="faq-list">

  <!-- Q1 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">1. Is Fort Kochi safe for solo travelers?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        Yes, Fort Kochi is widely considered one of the safest travel destinations in India. The local population is highly educated, tourist-friendly, and very helpful. Crime rates are extremely low, and the streets are generally peaceful and well-regarded.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q2 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">2. Is Fort Kochi safe for solo female travelers?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        Absolutely. Many solo female travelers visit Fort Kochi every year. The local culture is respectful, and catcalling is very rare. By taking standard precautions (like avoiding walking in poorly lit backalleys late at night and dressing modestly), you will have a very safe and comfortable trip.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q3 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">3. How much money do I need for a 3-day solo trip to Kochi?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        A budget of ₹3,000 to ₹5,000 is perfectly sufficient. If you stay in hostel dorms (₹500/night), eat traditional Kerala meals (₹120/meal), and use public ferries (₹6/ride), you can easily manage on ₹1,000 per day. If you prefer private homestays and dine at heritage cafes, plan for ₹2,500 to ₹3,500 per day.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q4 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">4. What is the best month to visit Fort Kochi?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        The best season to visit is from October to March. The weather is dry, pleasant, and slightly cooler, with lower humidity levels. December is popular due to the Cochin Carnival, though it is also the busiest and most expensive month.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q5 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">5. How do I reach Fort Kochi from Cochin International Airport (COK)?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        The airport is located 45 km away. The cheapest option is the air-conditioned KSRTC "KURTC" bus that runs directly from the airport terminal to Fort Kochi (fares around ₹100-₹150). Alternatively, you can take the metro from Aluva station to Ernakulam, or hire a pre-paid airport taxi for about ₹1,200 - ₹1,500.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q6 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">6. How do I reach Fort Kochi from Ernakulam Junction railway station?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        Take a short auto-rickshaw ride (₹60) from the station to the Ernakulam Jetty. From there, board the public wooden passenger ferry directly to Fort Kochi jetty. The ferry ride takes 20 minutes and costs just ₹6.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q7 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">7. Is the Kochi Water Metro worth trying?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        Yes, absolutely. The Kochi Water Metro is an award-winning, state-of-the-art public transit network using silent, air-conditioned electric catamarans. The ticket costs only ₹20 to ₹40 and offers a smooth, futuristic, and highly scenic commute across the backwaters.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q8 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">8. What is the difference between the public passenger ferry and the Water Metro?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        The public passenger ferry is a traditional wooden double-decker boat. It is non-AC, open-air, costs ₹6, and offers a retro, nostalgic local experience. The Water Metro is a modern electric catamaran, fully air-conditioned, silent, costs ₹20+, and operates from separate high-tech terminals. Both are excellent options.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q9 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">9. Do I need cash in Fort Kochi, or are card and mobile payments acceptable?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        You absolutely need cash. While boutique hotels and modern cafes accept cards and mobile UPI, local tea stalls, public ferries, ticket counters at palaces/synagogues, and auto-rickshaw drivers operate strictly on cash. Always carry ₹500 to ₹1,000 in small currency notes.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q10 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">10. Are there good hostels in Fort Kochi for solo travelers?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        Yes, Fort Kochi has a thriving hostel scene. Highly rated hostels like Zostel, GoStops, and various local boutique backpacker lodges are located right around Princess Street. They offer clean beds, high-speed internet, common rooms, and are excellent hubs for meeting other solo travelers.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q11 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">11. What are the best heritage cafés to visit?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        The top recommendations are Kashi Art Café (famed for carrot cake and breakfast), David Hall Gallery Café (great for garden-baked wood-fired pizzas), Alice Deli, and Teapot Café (famed for its vintage tea-themed colonial decor).
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q12 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">12. Can I swim in Fort Kochi Beach?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        No. Swimming is strictly prohibited at Fort Kochi Beach due to strong undercurrents, shipping lanes, and underwater granite seawalls. If you want to swim or sunbathe, take a day trip to Cherai Beach on Vypin Island.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q13 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">13. How many days are enough to explore Fort Kochi?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        Three days is the perfect duration. It gives you enough time to explore the heritage monuments, visit Jew Town and Mattancherry, watch a Kathakali performance, hop around the café scene, and take a relaxed boat cruise without feeling rushed.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q14 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">14. Can I explore Fort Kochi in just one day?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        Yes, but you will have to focus only on the highlights. A one-day trip would cover the Chinese Fishing Nets, St. Francis Church, Santa Cruz Basilica, and a quick auto ride to Mattancherry Palace and Jew Town before a sunset ferry back. It will feel a bit rushed, but it is entirely doable.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q15 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">15. Do I need to book Kathakali tickets in advance?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        During the peak winter tourist season (November to January), it is highly recommended to call or visit the Kerala Kathakali Centre in the morning to reserve your ticket. During the rest of the year, you can easily walk in and buy a ticket 30 minutes before the show.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q16 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">16. What is the entry fee for Mattancherry Palace?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        The ticket is extremely cheap: ₹5 for Indian citizens and ₹100 for foreign tourists. Children under 15 enter for free. Note that the palace is closed on Fridays.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q17 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">17. Is photography allowed inside the Paradesi Synagogue?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        No. Photography is strictly prohibited inside the Paradesi Synagogue to protect the historic items and maintain the sanctity of the space. You can photograph the exterior structure and the clock tower from the street.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q18 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">18. What language is spoken in Fort Kochi?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        The local language is Malayalam. However, English is very widely understood and spoken because Kochi is a historic trading port and a major tourism hub. You will have no trouble communicating in English or basic Hindi.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q19 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">19. How do I get to Cherai Beach from Fort Kochi?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        The most budget-friendly route is to take the public passenger ferry from Fort Kochi to Vypin Jetty (₹3, 5 minutes). From the Vypin bus stand (right outside the jetty), board a direct local bus heading to Cherai Beach (₹30, 45 minutes). You can also hire a taxi or auto, but it will be much more expensive.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q20 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">20. Are there vegetarian food options in Fort Kochi?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        Yes, absolutely. Kerala has a rich vegetarian food heritage. Sree Krishna Cafe serves wonderful vegetarian lunch meals, and every local restaurant offers vegetarian classics like Appam with vegetable stew, Puttu with Kadala curry, Idli, and Dosa.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q21 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">21. What is the local dress code in Fort Kochi?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        While Fort Kochi is relatively liberal, dressing conservatively is highly appreciated. Outfits that cover your shoulders and knees are recommended, especially when visiting churches, temples, or the synagogue. Swimwear is only acceptable on resort beaches, not public walking promenades.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q22 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">22. Is alcohol easily available in Fort Kochi?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        Alcohol is heavily regulated in Kerala. Most cafes and standard restaurants do not serve beer or spirits. Only hotels with five-star licenses or government-run BEVCO liquor outlets can sell alcohol. Some upscale heritage hotels have beer and wine licenses; ask before dining.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q23 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">23. Can I rent a bicycle or scooter in Fort Kochi?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        Yes. Many hostels and homestays rent out geared or standard bicycles for ₹100 to ₹150 per day. Scooter rentals (₹400-₹500/day) are also available at Loafer's Corner. You will need to leave a copy of your driver's license and passport as security.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q24 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">24. Are there mosquitoes in Fort Kochi?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        Yes, especially during and after the monsoons. Because of the water channels and lush vegetation, mosquitoes become active in the evenings. Always pack a good mosquito repellent cream or spray (like Odomos) and use mosquito nets or vaporizers in your room.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q25 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">25. Can I fly a drone in Fort Kochi?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        Generally, no. Fort Kochi is a sensitive military and industrial shipping corridor. It sits directly opposite the Southern Naval Command base and the Cochin Shipyard. The entire harbor mouth is a strictly enforced No-Fly Zone. Flying a drone without high-level written permission from civil aviation and defense authorities can lead to heavy fines and confiscation of your gear.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q26 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">26. What are the best souvenirs to buy in Jew Town?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        Top buys include fresh vacuum-sealed spices (cardamom, pepper, cinnamon), local tea and coffee powders, handmade coconut shell crafts, banana chips fried in coconut oil, aromatherapy oils, and miniature Kathakali masks.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q27 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">27. Is Fort Kochi crowded with tourists?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        Compared to other Indian tourist spots like Goa or Agra, Fort Kochi is relatively calm and uncrowded. The vibe is laid-back and intellectual. However, popular spots like the Chinese Nets and Jew Town can get busy on weekend evenings when locals visit.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q28 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">28. What are the operating timings of the Chinese Fishing Nets?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        The nets are active throughout the day, but the best times to watch them are early morning (6:00 AM – 8:00 AM) and evening (5:00 PM – 6:30 PM) when the tide is active and fish are moving near the shore.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q29 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">29. Where was Vasco da Gama buried in Fort Kochi?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        Vasco da Gama was originally buried inside the St. Francis Church after he died in Kochi in 1524. His body remained in the church for 14 years before his remains were exhumed and transported back to Lisbon, Portugal. The original tombstone is still visible and railed off inside the church.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q30 -->
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="faq-question">30. Is there high-speed internet available in hostels?</span>
      <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <div class="faq-answer-inner">
        Yes, almost all hostels and boutique homestays in Fort Kochi offer free, high-speed fiber Wi-Fi. Average speeds range from 50 Mbps to 100 Mbps, making it a very popular hub for digital nomads and remote workers.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>
